# Identify columns that need to be converted
columns_to_convert = ['adr']  # Example column names, add more as needed

# Convert the columns to numeric values
for col in columns_to_convert:
    data[col] = pd.to_numeric(data[col], errors='coerce')
In[49]:
# Handle any NaN values introduced by conversion
for col in columns_to_convert:
    data[col] = data[col].fillna(data[col].median())
In[51]:
# Select only the numerical columns
numerical_data = data.select_dtypes(include=['float64', 'int64'])

# Plot the correlation heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
correlation_matrix = numerical_data.corr()
sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm')
plt.title('Correlation Heatmap')
plt.show()

In[61]:
# Group by hotel type and calculate mean ADR
grouped_data = data.groupby('hotel')['adr'].mean()
grouped_data.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(10, 6))
plt.title('Average Daily Rate by Hotel Type')
plt.xlabel('Hotel Type')
plt.ylabel('Average Daily Rate (ADR)')
plt.show()
In[63]:
# Plot bookings by month
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
data['arrival_date_month'] = pd.Categorical(data['arrival_date_month'], categories=['January', 'February', 'March', 'April', 'May', 'June', 'July', 'August', 'September', 'October', 'November', 'December'], ordered=True)
monthly_bookings = data['arrival_date_month'].value_counts().sort_index()
monthly_bookings.plot(kind='bar')
plt.title('Monthly Bookings')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Number of Bookings')
plt.show()
In[]:
# Conclusion and Insights
1. The dataset had missing values in the columns 'children', 'country', 'agent', and 'company', which were handled appropriately.
2. The majority of bookings are for Resort Hotels compared to City Hotels.
3. The average daily rate (ADR) is generally higher for Resort Hotels.
4. Lead time distribution shows a high number of bookings made well in advance.
5. There are distinct booking patterns by month, with peaks in the summer months.
6. Correlation analysis indicates significant relationships between certain features, like lead time and ADR.
7. Additional features and visualizations provided deeper insights into the booking patterns and customer behavior.
